*   The [Robot Operating System](/Robot_Operating_System) (ROS) relies heavily on OpenCV, often using it as its primary vision package.
*   [VXL](/VXL) offers an alternative C++ library for computer vision tasks.
*   [CVIPtools](/CVIPtools) presents a comprehensive environment for computer vision and image processing, complete with a graphical user interface and C function libraries.
*   [OpenNN](/OpenNN) is another C++ library focused on [artificial neural networks](/Artificial_neural_network), also open-source.
*   The [List of free and open-source software packages](/List_of_free_and_open-source_software_packages) is an extensive catalog for the curious.
*   [MediaPipe](/MediaPipe), a framework from Google, is another notable player in the open-source space.

